  "texts": [
    "Output evaluationUnpredictability is a significant characteristic of large language models.",
    "Although instructed to provide an output with specific properties, an LLM could generate something that does not duly follow the user commands.",
    "For applications where predictability and reliability are crucial, the DSL contributes testing rule constructs aimed at validating the output of an asset (see Fig. 3).",
    "An output testing rule by expression defines a second asset validator that would be used to assess the target output, thus enabling a model-graded evaluation approach.",
    "On the other hand, individual traits of an asset would need to be reinforced due to their particular importance or relevance to the application, and so are properly indicated in order to be reassured."
  ],
